## Root Cause
The diff view was using `git diff --color=always` but difftastic (configured as `diff.external` in user's gitconfig) uses its own `DFT_COLOR` environment variable, not git's `--color` flag.

## Solution
Added `DFT_COLOR=always` to the git diff command in `PRHandlersService.ts:showDiff()`.

The fix respects user's git configuration:
- If user has difftastic as `diff.external` ‚Üí DFT_COLOR enables syntax highlighting
- If user has delta or default git diff ‚Üí `--color=always` still works

## Changes
- `src/services/keyboard/PRHandlersService.ts`: Added `DFT_COLOR=always` environment variable to the diff command

## Configuration Note
User's difftastic is properly configured in `~/nix/home.nix`:
```nix
programs.git.difftastic = {
  enable = true;
  enableAsDifftool = true;
  background = "dark";
};
```
This generates `diff.external = "difft --background dark"` in gitconfig.

