## Implementation Plan

### 1. Update PRWorkflow.checkMergeConflicts
Instead of file list comparison, perform an actual test merge:

```typescript
checkMergeConflicts = ({ beadId, projectPath }) =>
  Effect.gen(function* () {
    const worktreePath = yield* getWorktreePath(beadId, projectPath)

    // Fetch latest main
    yield* gitInWorktree(worktreePath, ["fetch", "origin", "main"])

    // Try merge with --no-commit to test
    const result = yield* gitInWorktree(worktreePath, 
      ["merge", "--no-commit", "--no-ff", "origin/main"]
    ).pipe(Effect.either)

    if (Either.isLeft(result)) {
      // Get conflict list
      const conflicts = yield* gitInWorktree(worktreePath, 
        ["diff", "--name-only", "--diff-filter=U"]
      )
      // Abort the test merge
      yield* gitInWorktree(worktreePath, ["merge", "--abort"])

      return {
        hasConflictRisk: true,
        conflictingFiles: conflicts.split('\n').filter(Boolean),
        canAutoMerge: false
      }
    }

    // Clean test merge succeeded - abort it (we'll do real merge after)
    yield* gitInWorktree(worktreePath, ["merge", "--abort"])
    return { hasConflictRisk: false, conflictingFiles: [], canAutoMerge: true }
  })
```

### 2. Update mergeToMain flow
- If `checkMergeConflicts` shows conflicts, DO NOT proceed
- Instead of confirmation dialog, show error with conflict file list
- User must resolve conflicts manually in worktree first

### 3. Files to modify
- `src/core/PRWorkflow.ts` - Update checkMergeConflicts and mergeToMain
- `src/services/keyboard/prHandlers.ts` - Update actionMergeToMain error handling
